from std.graphic takes spritesheet

~( ^.x.^)>
Load frames from a spritesheet and receive a shelf with keys for each frame.

It accepts the following argumments:
  1. The path to a spritesheet.
  2. A shelf of boxes holding the key and dimensions for each frame.
  (See the 'mewly.mews' source file for an example.)

It returns a shelf with keys for each frame, in the same order.
<(^.x.^ )~

😺 load_frames(sheet, frame_boxes)
  do spritesheet <- sheet, frame_boxes
  bring do std.map <- 🐈 (x) -> x.key, frame_boxes
~meow
